Bill Nye 'the Science Guy' joined President Barack Obama today for an Earth Day excursion, riding aboard Air Force One with the president during his visit to the Florida Everglades .
The White House said Tuesday that Nye, who has degrees in engineering but was made famous by his 90s era television show, would make the trek today .
On the road trip, Nye held court with press before boarding the airliner, telling them, 'We're going to #ActonClimate'